%N A394447 Number of tilings of the crook hexiamond spiral with n crook hexiamond tiles.
%C A394447 A simple manual method creates an infinite spiral with this tile (see animation in the link below).
%C A394447 Previous work with the sphinx tile produced 200 or so of the smallest frames that permit change. These frames were given the name "fundamental polyads" (see Links in A366704).
%C A394447 The ability to add one tile and get a small number of different tilings ends up being an ideal environment to compare tilings and discover the fundamental polyads for the crook hexiamond.
